#module #server #web

> HTTP server for the eshp web view. Serves cytoscape.js graph UI and SSE activity events (recall + scan).

eshp_server.py — stdlib http.server-based HTTP server (zero extra dependencies).

Routes:
  GET /                   → serve eshp/static/index.html
  GET /cytoscape.min.js   → serve bundled cytoscape.js (v3.33.4, no CDN — supply chain safety)
  GET /api/graph          → JSON: {elements: [...]} in cytoscape format (all notes + edges)
                            NOTE: edges where src or dst has no matching node are silently
                            filtered out — guards against ghost slugs crashing cytoscape
  GET /api/note/<slug>    → JSON: {slug, desc, body, tags, edges_out, edges_in}
  GET /events             → SSE stream: {"slug": "...", "type": "recall"|"scan"} on activity

SSE strategy:
  Each SSE client opens its own sqlite3 connection and polls both last_recalled_at
  and last_scanned_at via UNION query every 500ms.
  last_seen keyed by (slug, type) — scan and recall tracked independently.
  Seeds last_seen on connect to avoid replaying old events.
  Broken pipe / ConnectionResetError → clean disconnect.

Thread safety:
  Each request handler opens a fresh sqlite3.connect(check_same_thread=False).
  Do NOT share the write-side EshpStore with request handlers.

make_server(eshp_root: Path, host, port) → ThreadingHTTPServer
  Sets server.db_path = eshp_root / ".eshp.db" on the server instance.
  Does not start serving — call serve_forever() in a daemon thread.

TRAP — slug in /api/note/<slug> must be URL-decoded:
  Frontend calls encodeURIComponent(slug) → path-slugs like 'modules/cli' arrive
  as 'modules%2Fcli'. The handler uses urllib.parse.unquote() to decode before
  the DB lookup. Without this, path-slugs always 404 (was a real regression).


  The SSE /events handler runs an infinite poll loop for the duration of the
  browser session. HTTPServer is single-threaded: once /events is accepted, the
  entire server is blocked — no further requests (including /api/note/<slug>)
  can be served. ThreadingHTTPServer gives each connection its own thread.

Static files live in eshp/static/ relative to eshp_server.py:
  index.html        — SPA with cytoscape + SSE listener
  cytoscape.min.js  — bundled (do not load from CDN)

